When I read about Todd Akin&rsquo;s unfortunate comments to Charles Jaco, my first thought was uncharitable. &ldquo;I could just kill him.&rdquo;
&ldquo;I could kill him,&rdquo; is an idiom. Its cousins include &ldquo;wring his neck&rdquo; and &ldquo;poke his eyes out.&rdquo; Idioms hyperbolize our emotional reaction to an event.
I was angry because Todd Akin gave the left a great talking point in the infamous interview. I like Todd Akin. I voted for him.
